        text: "Chocolate starts its journey as a fruit on the cacao tree. These trees grow in hot, rainy places near the equator. Inside the fruit are large seeds called cacao beans. These beans are very bitter and do not taste like chocolate at all when they are fresh.\n\nAfter the beans are harvested, they are fermented and dried in the sun. Then, they are sent to factories where they are roasted and ground into a thick liquid. To make the chocolate we love, manufacturers add sugar, cocoa butter, and sometimes milk.\n\nThe mixture is stirred for a long time to make it smooth. Finally, it is cooled and shaped into bars. Chocolate was once a drink for Aztec kings, but today it is enjoyed by almost everyone. Dark chocolate is even considered healthy in small amounts because it has antioxidants." 
